Recording unmodified. Dueting calls. Minimum of 7 individuals. One pair of laughingthrushes was perched on the handrail along a path at Kent Ridge Park. This first pair was calling to a second pair ~4 meters away perched in the trees. A third pair flew in and also perched on the handrail, closely followed by a 7th solitary bird. Vocalization did not begin until I approached. Time ~7:00 pm, just before sunset. The loudest call in this recording is the duet of the first pair, the slightly quieter call is the duet of the second pair.
